514
00:34:13,584 --> 00:34:17,179
trapped by a wife who
suffocates you with forgiveness.

515
00:34:17,255 --> 00:34:20,281
<i>You're looking</i>
<i>for a way out. </i>

516
00:34:20,358 --> 00:34:21,518
Yeah.

517
00:34:21,592 --> 00:34:24,322
Something final...

518
00:34:24,395 --> 00:34:26,522
without remorse...

519
00:34:26,597 --> 00:34:28,963
<i>without regret. </i>

520
00:34:29,033 --> 00:34:34,130
Wherever there is hate,
violence, depravity...

521
00:34:34,205 --> 00:34:37,140
a door
will always be found.

522
00:34:39,277 --> 00:34:43,373
<i>This musical puzzle... </i>

523
00:34:43,448 --> 00:34:49,444
<i>created by a Frenchman</i>
<i>named L'merchant. </i>

524
00:34:58,262 --> 00:35:01,527
<i>Merchant and Sage: It is a means
to break the surface of the real. </i>

525
00:35:07,371 --> 00:35:11,034
[Wind whistles]

526
00:35:27,725 --> 00:35:29,590
[Rumbling]

527
00:35:29,660 --> 00:35:33,596
[Bottles rattle]

528
00:35:37,001 --> 00:35:39,936
[Electricity crackles]

529
00:36:13,771 --> 00:36:16,899
Agggh!

530
00:36:16,974 --> 00:36:19,204
Ugh! Agh!

531
00:36:19,277 --> 00:36:22,246
Which do you find
more exhilarating, Trevor...

532
00:36:22,313 --> 00:36:24,941
the pain or the pleasure?

533
00:36:25,016 --> 00:36:29,043
Personally, I prefer pain.

534
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:31,645
Agggh!

535
00:36:34,225 --> 00:36:36,591
Is there something wrong?

536
00:36:40,731 --> 00:36:42,323
No.

537
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,492
[Coughs]

538
00:36:43,568 --> 00:36:46,196
No, I'm okay.

539
00:36:46,270 --> 00:36:48,465
[Cellular phone rings]

540
00:36:50,241 --> 00:36:52,573
Shall I get that for you?

541
00:36:52,643 --> 00:37:00,108
[Ringing continues]

542
00:37:04,355 --> 00:37:05,117
Hello?

543
00:37:05,189 --> 00:37:09,216
<i>This is Detective Givens,</i>
<i>Mike's partner. </i>

544
00:37:09,293 --> 00:37:11,386
But I don't...
I don't understand.

545
00:37:11,462 --> 00:37:14,431
How could this be a... a homicide
case when there was no murder?

546
00:37:14,498 --> 00:37:16,193
The last time anybody saw
this woman, she was alive.

547
00:37:16,267 --> 00:37:17,734
You seem pretty certain
that she's dead.

548
00:37:17,802 --> 00:37:23,570
Hey, detective, I saw
my wife drown in our car.

549
00:37:23,641 --> 00:37:25,199
Yeah.

550
00:37:25,276 --> 00:37:27,005
Right.

551
00:37:27,078 --> 00:37:29,342
You know, I've done
my homework on you, man.

552
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:32,246
You're, uh... you're real smart
with numbers, aren't you?

553
00:37:32,316 --> 00:37:34,079
Where are you going
with this?

554
00:37:34,151 --> 00:37:37,018
How many zeros
was your wife worth?

555
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:38,851
We had nothing.

556
00:37:38,923 --> 00:37:39,855
<i>No. </i>

557
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:41,824
<i>You</i> had nothing.

558
00:37:41,892 --> 00:37:44,258
She had a nice little
inheritance

559
00:37:44,328 --> 00:37:46,489
<i>stashed away</i>
<i>for a rainy day. </i>

560
00:37:46,564 --> 00:37:49,692
Uh...
I'm sorry, what?

561
00:37:52,837 --> 00:37:55,203
Don't play fucking stupid
with me, all right?

562
00:37:55,273 --> 00:37:57,537
Kirsty's father
and Uncle Frank

563
00:37:57,608 --> 00:38:00,441
had several sizeable
financial holdings

564
00:38:00,511 --> 00:38:02,604
when they passed away...

565
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:07,515
under some rather, uh...
unusual circumstances.

566
00:38:07,585 --> 00:38:09,280
You know...
I- I don't know.

567
00:38:09,353 --> 00:38:12,015
Kirsty, she never liked
to talk about her past.

568
00:38:12,089 --> 00:38:14,990
Well, maybe that's because
she didn't really trust you.

569
00:38:15,059 --> 00:38:17,152
It seems that she's
the sole beneficiary,

570
00:38:17,228 --> 00:38:19,128
so if Kirsty's dead,

571
00:38:19,196 --> 00:38:22,165
like you seem
so fucking certain,

572
00:38:22,233 --> 00:38:24,360
<i>well, then,</i>
<i>I guess it all</i>...

573
00:38:24,435 --> 00:38:26,665
<i>well, it all goes to you,</i>
<i>Trev. </i>

574
00:38:26,737 --> 00:38:30,332
I swear to God, man, I don't
know anything about that.

575
00:38:30,408 --> 00:38:32,137
[Sighs]

576
00:38:32,209 --> 00:38:33,403
Hmm.

577
00:38:33,477 --> 00:38:34,739
[Snaps fingers]

578
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:37,542
My partner...
Detective Lange...

579
00:38:37,615 --> 00:38:39,879
he's a little softer
around the heart than I am.

580
00:38:39,950 --> 00:38:42,612
<i>Me, uh... </i>
<i>I'm hard as they come. </i>

581
00:38:42,687 --> 00:38:46,623
When I get a feeling about
something, I'm usually right.

582
00:38:46,691 --> 00:38:50,320
And I got a bad feeling
about you, Trev.

583
00:38:51,762 --> 00:38:54,822
Real bad.

584
00:38:54,932 --> 00:38:57,594
<i>You're obsessed</i>
<i>with that thing. </i>

585
00:38:57,668 --> 00:39:00,603
God forbid we let one event
go unrecorded.

586
00:39:00,671 --> 00:39:03,799
<i>Why don't you come to bed?</i>
<i>Please? Please?</i>

587
00:39:03,874 --> 00:39:06,775
<i>It's our anniversary, Trevor. </i>
<i>Come on. </i>

588
00:39:06,844 --> 00:39:08,539
<i>Trevor:</i>
<i>First things first. </i>

589
00:39:08,612 --> 00:39:11,012
[Click]

590
00:39:14,151 --> 00:39:16,051
[Indistinct shouting]

591
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:17,587
[Siren wailing]

592
00:39:17,655 --> 00:39:19,555
Just like I thought.

593
00:39:19,623 --> 00:39:20,988
Nothing.

594
00:39:21,058 --> 00:39:22,958
[Chuckles]

595
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:38,130
[Knocking]

596
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:40,607
Hey.

597
00:39:40,678 --> 00:39:42,270
<i>Can I, um... </i>

598
00:39:42,346 --> 00:39:44,371
borrow something?

599
00:39:46,917 --> 00:39:48,384
Um...

600
00:39:48,452 --> 00:39:50,682
Yeah, sure.
What do you want?

601
00:39:50,755 --> 00:39:51,744
You.

602
00:39:53,691 --> 00:39:54,817
Uh...

603
00:39:54,892 --> 00:39:55,881
Now...

604
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,292
I'm feeling kind of
weird here, you know?

605
00:39:59,330 --> 00:40:01,730
[Sighs]

606
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:03,323
[Scoffs]

607
00:40:06,303 --> 00:40:07,565
It's getting hot in here,
no?

608
00:40:11,642 --> 00:40:13,974
<i>You</i> are <i>being kind of... </i>

609
00:40:14,044 --> 00:40:15,944
weird.

610
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:18,812
It's almost like...

611
00:40:21,185 --> 00:40:23,278
I'm with somebody else.

612
00:40:23,354 --> 00:40:26,323
[Chuckles]

613
00:40:26,390 --> 00:40:28,756
[Ripping, moans]

614
00:40:32,496 --> 00:40:35,021
Tie me up.

615
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:36,999
[Clears throat]

616
00:40:37,067 --> 00:40:38,830
Come and get it.

617
00:40:38,903 --> 00:40:40,928
<i>Come on. </i>

618
00:40:43,340 --> 00:40:45,865
<i>That's it. </i>

619
00:40:45,943 --> 00:40:47,604
<i>[Chuckles]</i>

620
00:40:59,757 --> 00:41:02,282
[Moans]

621
00:41:06,430 --> 00:41:07,727
[Gasps]

622
00:41:08,599 --> 00:41:10,123
Uhh!

623
00:41:10,201 --> 00:41:11,998
Ohh!

624
00:41:14,205 --> 00:41:14,967
Ohh!

625
00:41:15,039 --> 00:41:16,199
Uhh!

626
00:41:16,907 --> 00:41:18,568
<i>Aah!</i>

627
00:41:19,610 --> 00:41:20,907
<i>Aah!</i>

628
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:23,177
[Clanking]

629
00:41:26,250 --> 00:41:27,877
[Gasps]

630
00:41:27,952 --> 00:41:29,886
[Panting]

631
00:41:54,612 --> 00:41:56,603
[Gasps]

632
00:41:59,316 --> 00:42:02,774
[Panting]

633
00:42:07,424 --> 00:42:10,359
[Faucet handles squeak,
water running]

634
00:42:14,932 --> 00:42:16,058
Aah!

635
00:42:18,969 --> 00:42:21,369
All problems solved.

636
00:42:23,874 --> 00:42:26,434
[Water dripping]

637
00:42:59,476 --> 00:43:02,001
[Birds chirping]

638
00:43:07,351 --> 00:43:10,377
[Indistinct shouting,
dog barking]

639
00:43:20,531 --> 00:43:23,261
[Baby crying]

640
00:43:37,114 --> 00:43:39,105
Uh...

641
00:43:40,751 --> 00:43:41,809
Man, you're alive.

642
00:43:41,885 --> 00:43:42,817
Ohh!

643
00:43:42,886 --> 00:43:45,855
I have some serious
space issues.

644
00:43:45,923 --> 00:43:47,515
What... did you want?

645
00:43:47,591 --> 00:43:50,185
Uh, right. Um...

646
00:43:50,260 --> 00:43:51,784
We need to talk...

647
00:43:51,862 --> 00:43:54,228
you know, about what we did
last night.

648
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:56,493
[Chuckles] W-What?

649
00:43:56,567 --> 00:43:59,365
<i>Man: Who the fuck is it?!</i>

650
00:43:59,436 --> 00:44:00,835
Who's in there with you?

651
00:44:00,904 --> 00:44:02,963
Are you having
a nervous breakdown

652
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:05,099
or something?

653
00:44:05,175 --> 00:44:06,199
Hey.

654
00:44:06,276 --> 00:44:08,642
What can we do for you,
chief?

655
00:44:10,280 --> 00:44:11,372
Who are you?

656
00:44:11,448 --> 00:44:13,143
[Chuckles]

657
00:44:13,217 --> 00:44:16,482
If you know Tawny,
you better know me, pal.

658
00:44:16,553 --> 00:44:19,579
Hey, uh, I'm sorry.
It's my mistake.

659
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:21,591
I'll talk to you later.

660
00:44:25,596 --> 00:44:28,360
Let's make it <i>much</i> later!

661
00:44:32,302 --> 00:44:33,234
[Giggles]

662
00:44:33,303 --> 00:44:34,736
[Smack]
Get in there.

663
00:44:35,072 --> 00:44:36,039
[Answering machine clicks]

664
00:44:36,106 --> 00:44:37,539
<i>Trevor: Hey,</i>
<i>we're not in right now. </i>

665
00:44:37,608 --> 00:44:39,132
<i>Leave a message</i>
<i>after the beep. Thanks. </i>

666
00:44:39,209 --> 00:44:40,403
[Beep]

667
00:44:40,477 --> 00:44:42,945
<i>This is Detective Lange,</i>
<i>Trevor. </i>

668
00:44:43,013 --> 00:44:45,106
<i>We need to talk</i>
<i>as soon as possible. </i>

669
00:44:45,182 --> 00:44:47,810
<i>There's been an interesting</i>
<i>twist in the puzzle. </i>

670
00:44:47,885 --> 00:44:50,479
[Indistinct conversations,
telephones ringing]

671
00:44:50,554 --> 00:44:53,045
<i>Detective Givens: I'm telling you
right now your boy killed the boss. </i>

672
00:44:53,123 --> 00:44:54,420
<i>As sure</i>
<i>as I am standing here. </i>

673
00:44:54,491 --> 00:44:56,356
[Laughter]

674
00:44:56,427 --> 00:44:58,861
<i>Detective Lange: No, I'm not
too sure about the wife. </i>

675
00:44:58,929 --> 00:45:00,692
<i>It's done. </i>

676
00:45:02,299 --> 00:45:05,666
What are you doing
to find my wife?

677
00:45:05,736 --> 00:45:07,761
Well, I can assure you

678
00:45:07,838 --> 00:45:10,238
<i>we're doing everything in our
power to find your wife, Trevor. </i>

679
00:45:10,307 --> 00:45:12,798
<i>This investigation</i>
<i>is gonna take some time. </i>

680
00:45:12,876 --> 00:45:15,470
<i>I'm gonna need your full</i>
<i>cooperation on this. </i>

681
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:18,014
What about that message you left
on my answering machine?

682
00:45:18,082 --> 00:45:21,779
What's your relationship
with Gwen Stevens?

683
00:45:21,852 --> 00:45:23,080
What?

684
00:45:25,022 --> 00:45:26,455
We appreciate you
coming down.

685
00:45:26,523 --> 00:45:28,718
- <i>You've been very helpful. </i>
- <i>Yeah, thanks. </i>

686
00:45:28,792 --> 00:45:30,817
- So that's all for now?
- Yeah.

687
00:45:34,698 --> 00:45:35,926
What?

688
00:45:39,737 --> 00:45:40,999
She was my boss.

689
00:45:41,071 --> 00:45:42,231
And that's it?

690
00:45:42,306 --> 00:45:43,568
Yeah, that's it.

691
00:45:43,640 --> 00:45:46,268
What did <i>he</i> tell you?

692
00:45:46,343 --> 00:45:47,867
Nothing.

693
00:45:47,945 --> 00:45:51,904
We leave no stone unturned
around here, Trevor.

694
00:45:51,982 --> 00:45:53,643
You think I did it.

695
00:45:53,717 --> 00:45:55,742
Hey,
I'm on your side here.

696
00:45:55,819 --> 00:45:59,687
Then would you please tell me
what the <i>fuck</i> is going on?

697
00:45:59,757 --> 00:46:02,248
I wish I knew.

698
00:46:02,326 --> 00:46:05,090
Yeah. I'll bet.

699
00:46:12,936 --> 00:46:14,426
[Door closes]

700
00:46:38,095 --> 00:46:43,226
<i>Once you choose to open the
bo x and unleash its power,</i>

701
00:46:43,300 --> 00:46:45,632
there is no returning.

702
00:46:45,702 --> 00:46:47,727
<i>And are you willing</i>
<i>to pay the price?</i>

703
00:46:49,773 --> 00:46:52,742
[Fly buzzing]

704
00:46:52,810 --> 00:46:56,041
No, the price
is far greater,

705
00:46:56,113 --> 00:46:57,671
<i>but you'll learn that. </i>

706
00:47:00,884 --> 00:47:02,977
They <i>all</i> do.

707
00:47:03,053 --> 00:47:05,021
[Wings flapping]

708
00:47:06,423 --> 00:47:06,855
Whoa!

709
00:47:08,425 --> 00:47:10,518
Hey.

710
00:47:10,594 --> 00:47:12,221
You okay?

711
00:47:12,296 --> 00:47:14,059
Yeah, I know,
I was just... you know.

712
00:47:14,131 --> 00:47:15,655
[Chuckles softly]

713
00:47:15,732 --> 00:47:17,324
Can I get you anything?

714
00:47:17,401 --> 00:47:20,996
Uh, no.
No. I'm okay.

715
00:47:34,051 --> 00:47:37,043
[Siren wails in distance]

716
00:47:45,329 --> 00:47:47,320
[Man gasping]

717
00:48:02,946 --> 00:48:04,208
You okay?

718
00:48:04,281 --> 00:48:07,512
I don't know, Allison.
I think I, um...

719
00:48:07,584 --> 00:48:09,552
I think I really
screwed everything up.

720
00:48:09,620 --> 00:48:11,611
Come on, Trevor.
You can't blame yourself.

721
00:48:11,688 --> 00:48:13,781
Yeah.

722
00:48:17,528 --> 00:48:19,018
I miss her.

723
00:48:21,865 --> 00:48:24,425
I miss my wife.

724
00:48:30,908 --> 00:48:33,274
It sounds like you're
remembering more and more,

725
00:48:33,343 --> 00:48:35,743
and that's a good thing,
Trevor.

726
00:48:35,813 --> 00:48:39,442
Maybe you're not the angel
that you thought you were.

727
00:48:39,516 --> 00:48:42,212
[Chuckles softly]
Yeah.

728
00:48:42,286 --> 00:48:44,948
Come on. You're gonna
get through this, Trevor.

729
00:48:50,494 --> 00:48:52,121
[Telephone rings]

730
00:48:52,196 --> 00:48:53,629
Hey, Bret...

731
00:48:53,697 --> 00:48:55,927
Come here.
We need to talk.

732
00:48:55,999 --> 00:48:57,830
Look, Trev,
I'm really, really busy.

733
00:48:57,901 --> 00:48:59,801
I got a stack of reports
due by 3:00.

734
00:48:59,870 --> 00:49:02,236
The suits upstairs are all
over my ass on this one, okay?

735
00:49:02,306 --> 00:49:04,934
- What'd you tell the police?
- Nothing they didn't already know.

736
00:49:05,008 --> 00:49:06,270
What's that
supposed to mean?

737
00:49:06,343 --> 00:49:08,470
I didn't tell them anything
they didn't already know.

738
00:49:08,545 --> 00:49:11,241
Hey, Bret, why don't you help me
out here, man? They think I did it.

739
00:49:11,315 --> 00:49:12,543
Did what?

740
00:49:12,616 --> 00:49:14,311
Killed Kirsty.

741
00:49:14,384 --> 00:49:18,184
I got a... report
to... do.

742
00:49:20,724 --> 00:49:23,249
Just make yourself
at home.

743
00:49:23,327 --> 00:49:25,625
Oh, already have.

744
00:49:25,696 --> 00:49:27,926
[Telephones ringing
in distance]

745
00:49:27,998 --> 00:49:30,592
Why are you here,
detective?

746
00:49:30,667 --> 00:49:34,068
We found this curious
little object

747
00:49:34,138 --> 00:49:37,437
<i>not too far from the site</i>
<i>of the accident. </i>

748
00:49:37,508 --> 00:49:39,442
No prints.

749
00:49:39,510 --> 00:49:43,276
Forensics scraped a little dark
residue that was caked on it.

750
00:49:43,347 --> 00:49:46,783
Want to take a guess
what they found?

751
00:49:46,850 --> 00:49:49,944
Uh, no, but somethin' tells
me that you're gonna tell me.

752
00:49:50,020 --> 00:49:51,578
Blood, Trevor.

753
00:49:51,655 --> 00:49:54,647
Matched some of the blood we
took from the seat of your car.

754
00:49:54,725 --> 00:49:56,454
Can you tell me
anything about it?

755
00:49:56,527 --> 00:49:58,222
I- I-I... It...

756
00:49:58,295 --> 00:50:00,490
[Sighs] It looks familiar,
you know?

757
00:50:00,564 --> 00:50:02,259
Like most things
these days.

758
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:04,027
I- I think
it was in the car.

759
00:50:04,101 --> 00:50:06,831
Gee... you think so?

760
00:50:06,904 --> 00:50:10,635
Think about it, Trevor.

761
00:50:10,707 --> 00:50:12,834
Give me something
to go on here.

762
00:50:12,910 --> 00:50:17,244
I got Givens ready to drag
you in today on murder charges.

763
00:50:17,314 --> 00:50:21,045
Help me get him off my back...
off of <i>your</i> back.

764
00:50:21,118 --> 00:50:22,983
It was an accident,
detective,

765
00:50:23,053 --> 00:50:25,283
just like I've been saying
all along.

766
00:50:25,355 --> 00:50:26,549
Somebody's gotta believe me.

767
00:50:26,623 --> 00:50:27,988
[Telephone ringing
in distance]

768
00:50:28,058 --> 00:50:29,320
I believe you, Trevor.

769
00:50:29,393 --> 00:50:30,951
[Chuckles] Yeah.

770
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:33,053
But so far...

771
00:50:33,130 --> 00:50:35,428
I'm the only one who does.

772
00:50:52,950 --> 00:50:55,646
[Footsteps approach]

773
00:50:55,719 --> 00:50:57,186
<i>Hey. </i>

774
00:50:57,254 --> 00:51:00,246
Look, I-I'm sorry, okay?
We need to talk.

775
00:51:02,226 --> 00:51:05,423
[Gurgles]

776
00:51:05,495 --> 00:51:07,122
What's up?

777
00:51:07,197 --> 00:51:10,189
It's getting a little weird
around here, so, um... [Sighs]

778
00:51:10,267 --> 00:51:11,825
I quit.
Today's my last day.

779
00:51:11,902 --> 00:51:13,392
You know, I figured
it was the perfect time

780
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:15,700
to say "Fuck you" to the morons
around here and make a serious change.

781
00:51:15,772 --> 00:51:17,569
Well, now, Bret, that's...
that's... [Door opens]

782
00:51:19,576 --> 00:51:21,373
[Coins rattle]

783
00:51:21,445 --> 00:51:23,675
[Machine beeps]

784
00:51:23,747 --> 00:51:25,237
[Bag falls]

785
00:51:26,984 --> 00:51:28,315
[Door closes]

786
00:51:28,385 --> 00:51:31,013
Look, uh... i know you got your,
uh, golden egg all lined up,

787
00:51:31,088 --> 00:51:34,057
and that's cool, but the rest of us
gotta make some hay for ourselves,

788
00:51:34,124 --> 00:51:36,592
'cause frankly, this job
ain't paying the bills anymore.

789
00:51:36,660 --> 00:51:39,356
We're not all drinking from the
cash cow, like your wife was.

790
00:51:40,831 --> 00:51:42,696
What are you talking about?

791
00:51:42,766 --> 00:51:44,256
What am I talking about?

792
00:51:44,334 --> 00:51:45,266
Yeah.

793
00:51:45,335 --> 00:51:46,267
The money.

794
00:51:46,336 --> 00:51:47,598
[Camera whirs, beeps]

795
00:51:47,671 --> 00:51:49,639
Don't play stupid, man...
Kirsty's inheritance.

796
00:51:49,706 --> 00:51:52,140
I'm talking about
the plan.

797
00:51:52,209 --> 00:51:53,972
You know,
let's get out of here.

798
00:51:54,044 --> 00:51:55,909
Oh, whoa, whoa.
Hey, whoa, whoa, Bret.

799
00:51:55,979 --> 00:51:57,446
What did you tell Lange?

800
00:51:57,514 --> 00:52:00,244
- Oh, come on, Trev. What the hell's wrong with...
- No, no, no!

801
00:52:00,317 --> 00:52:03,286
Did you tell him about Gwen...
a- about the inheritance?

802
00:52:03,353 --> 00:52:05,287
I didn't tell him
anything.

803
00:52:06,890 --> 00:52:09,051
You know, we're all here
for you, Trev.

804
00:52:09,526 --> 00:52:11,926
Agh! God!

805
00:52:11,995 --> 00:52:14,293
Agh!

806
00:52:15,732 --> 00:52:17,597
[Groans]

807
00:52:19,303 --> 00:52:21,134
<i>I trusted you!</i>
<i>Goddamn it!</i>

808
00:52:21,204 --> 00:52:22,569
<i>How could you do this</i>
<i>to us?!</i>

809
00:52:22,639 --> 00:52:24,072
[Glass shatters]
God!

810
00:52:25,242 --> 00:52:26,834
Shit.

811
00:52:26,910 --> 00:52:28,309
God!

812
00:52:28,378 --> 00:52:29,845
<i> Jesus, buddy. </i>
<i>You all right?</i>

813
00:52:31,181 --> 00:52:32,614
Shit.
I gotta go, man.

814
00:52:32,683 --> 00:52:35,743
Well, let me
give you a...

815
00:52:35,819 --> 00:52:37,081
a ride.

816
00:52:39,056 --> 00:52:40,614
[Grunting]

817
00:52:40,691 --> 00:52:43,023
[Hydraulic hiss]

818
00:52:43,093 --> 00:52:45,027
[Roaring]
Agh!

819
00:52:47,097 --> 00:52:48,655
[Beeps]

820
00:52:48,732 --> 00:52:50,427
[Groans]

821
00:52:50,500 --> 00:52:52,661
Yeah. Hello.
Yeah, hi.

822
00:52:52,736 --> 00:52:56,604
Um, I'd like to speak
to Dr. Allison Dormire.

823
00:52:57,941 --> 00:53:01,274
Hello. Yeah, hi.

824
00:53:01,345 --> 00:53:04,075
What do you mean
she's not there?

825
00:53:04,147 --> 00:53:07,275
S- She's <i>always</i> there.
She's a resident.

826
00:53:07,351 --> 00:53:08,875
All right, hey, look...

827
00:53:08,952 --> 00:53:12,319
Can you... can you please
help me find her? Please?

828
00:53:12,389 --> 00:53:14,653
Hello?

829
00:53:14,725 --> 00:53:16,056
Damn it.

830
00:53:24,568 --> 00:53:25,796
Damn.

831
00:53:25,869 --> 00:53:27,894
<i>Sage: There's</i>
<i>no physical explanation</i>

832
00:53:27,971 --> 00:53:30,030
<i>for these headaches</i>
<i>of yours, Trevor. </i>

833
00:53:30,107 --> 00:53:32,803
Your body's
completely healed.

834
00:53:32,876 --> 00:53:36,539
If there is any pain
in your head...

835
00:53:36,613 --> 00:53:38,513
it's in your head.

836
00:53:41,318 --> 00:53:45,550
Your soul... is locked up
inside you,

837
00:53:45,622 --> 00:53:48,887
and you need to free it,
Trevor.

838
00:53:48,959 --> 00:53:51,257
You blocked yourself
from the healing process,

839
00:53:51,328 --> 00:53:53,193
and that's what
we need to do now...

840
00:53:53,263 --> 00:53:56,130
heal your soul.

841
00:53:56,199 --> 00:53:59,999
The only way to do that
is to give in utterly.

842
00:54:00,070 --> 00:54:03,039
Do you know what I mean
by giving in?

843
00:54:03,106 --> 00:54:05,666
No.

844
00:54:05,742 --> 00:54:07,505
It's about trust.

845
00:54:07,577 --> 00:54:11,946
Do you trust me...
implicitly?

846
00:54:12,015 --> 00:54:14,142
I don't know
what's real...

847
00:54:14,217 --> 00:54:16,378
or what isn't real anymore.

848
00:54:16,453 --> 00:54:19,320
How can I trust anybody?

849
00:54:28,899 --> 00:54:30,526
You can trust me.

850
00:54:35,472 --> 00:54:40,933
Surrender yourself
to your past.

851
00:54:41,011 --> 00:54:44,105
<i>It's the only way you're</i>
<i>gonna become whole again. </i>

852
00:54:49,886 --> 00:54:54,482
Are you willing
to partake?

853
00:55:32,863 --> 00:55:35,855
[Siren wails]

854
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:39,498
<i>Can you hear me?</i>
<i> Just nod. </i>

855
00:55:39,569 --> 00:55:43,232
<i>You know where you are?</i>

856
00:55:43,306 --> 00:55:44,637
Ambulance.

857
00:55:44,708 --> 00:55:46,198
Remember what happened
back there?

858
00:55:46,276 --> 00:55:50,372
Some woman on top of me
naked, trying to kill me.

859
00:55:50,447 --> 00:55:52,608
Uh, yeah,
not quite that good.

860
00:55:52,682 --> 00:55:54,775
Um, you were riding
on a bus,

861
00:55:54,851 --> 00:55:57,376
and then you just collapsed
onto the floor, out cold.

862
00:55:57,454 --> 00:55:59,285
Do you remember
riding on a bus now?

863
00:55:59,356 --> 00:56:00,789
No.

864
00:56:00,857 --> 00:56:02,688
Oh...

865
00:56:02,759 --> 00:56:04,886
Maybe. I don't...

866
00:56:04,961 --> 00:56:08,897
<i>[Wheels squeaking]</i>

867
00:56:15,071 --> 00:56:16,129
<i>Hello, Trevor. </i>

868
00:56:16,206 --> 00:56:18,674
Well, what'd you do
this time?

869
00:56:18,742 --> 00:56:21,370
Oh, yeah, couple of stitches
will fix that right up.

870
00:56:21,444 --> 00:56:23,139
Hey, where's Allison?

871
00:56:23,213 --> 00:56:25,147
- Allison?
- Yeah, Allison Dormire.

872
00:56:25,215 --> 00:56:27,649
<i>She</i>...
<i>She's a resident here. </i>

873
00:56:27,717 --> 00:56:31,016
<i>I'm sorry. We don't have any
resident by the name of Allison. </i>

874
00:56:31,087 --> 00:56:33,282
Look, my nurse will
numb this up, and, uh...

875
00:56:33,356 --> 00:56:36,382
I'll get right back
to you.

876
00:56:36,459 --> 00:56:39,656
<i>Nurse: It's imperative</i>
<i>that you stay calm. </i>

877
00:56:40,997 --> 00:56:42,897
<i>This might sting a little. </i>

878
00:56:42,966 --> 00:56:44,991
<i> Just relax, Trevor. </i>

879
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:47,468
- Remember, we're all...
- You're all here for me. Go ahead, say it.

880
00:56:47,537 --> 00:56:50,005
Jesus Christ!
I'm so tired of this shit!

881
00:56:50,073 --> 00:56:52,564
- Trevor! Trevor!
- <i>I'm tired of all you people. </i>

882
00:57:08,158 --> 00:57:10,058
Okay, you caught me.

883
00:57:10,126 --> 00:57:12,060
At least let me finish,
will ya?

884
00:57:12,128 --> 00:57:14,153
<i>I got one puff left. </i>

885
00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:16,198
Knock yourself out.

886
00:57:19,135 --> 00:57:22,229
<i>Trevor? I heard you were looking
for me.  Is everything all right?</i>

887
00:57:22,305 --> 00:57:24,432
Allison, hey.

888
00:57:25,675 --> 00:57:26,699
No.

889
00:57:26,776 --> 00:57:28,801
I'm not all right.

890
00:57:28,878 --> 00:57:30,846
Look, I, um...

891
00:57:30,914 --> 00:57:36,546
think I've done some very...
<i>very</i> bad things.

892
00:57:36,620 --> 00:57:40,249
<i>Everybody does things</i>
<i>they regret. </i>

893
00:57:40,323 --> 00:57:43,622
It's part of life.

894
00:57:43,693 --> 00:57:47,094
Until now, you couldn't
remember parts of your past,

895
00:57:47,163 --> 00:57:49,131
and now they're all
hitting you at once.

896
00:57:49,199 --> 00:57:50,598
It's a shock
to the system.

897
00:57:50,667 --> 00:57:52,692
You can't undo your past.

898
00:57:52,769 --> 00:57:56,830
And sooner or later, you're
gonna have to confront it.

899
00:57:56,906 --> 00:57:58,498
And it frightens me
to think

900
00:57:58,575 --> 00:58:02,011
that I can't be there
for you when you do.

901
00:58:07,651 --> 00:58:10,643
- <i>Hey, buddy... </i>
- Yeah, but I was starting to think I was going,

902
00:58:10,720 --> 00:58:12,187
<i>you know,</i>
<i>insane or something. </i>

903
00:58:12,255 --> 00:58:14,086
- <i>Hey, buddy... </i>
- What?!

904
00:58:14,157 --> 00:58:17,456
Who the hell
are you talkin' to?

905
00:58:37,447 --> 00:58:39,210
- Agh!
- <i>What have you done?!</i>

906
00:58:39,282 --> 00:58:42,547
<i>Detective Lange: What's your
relationship with Gwen Stevens?</i>

907
00:58:42,619 --> 00:58:45,782
I know about Gwen...
and the others.

908
00:58:49,793 --> 00:58:51,226
What the fuck?

909
00:58:54,464 --> 00:58:55,294
Aaah!

910
00:58:55,365 --> 00:58:57,390
<i>[Squealing]</i>

911
00:59:07,377 --> 00:59:10,312
[Thunder crashes]

912
00:59:15,885 --> 00:59:19,048
[Water dripping slowly]

913
00:59:37,674 --> 00:59:39,938
Where are you?

914
00:59:40,009 --> 00:59:41,738
What have you done
to me?

915
00:59:41,811 --> 00:59:44,177
Fuck.

916
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:46,613
What the fuck
is happening to me?

917
00:59:46,683 --> 00:59:49,208
[Groans]

918
00:59:49,285 --> 00:59:50,582
[Crash]

919
00:59:50,653 --> 00:59:54,111
Where are you,
Goddamn it?!

920
00:59:54,190 --> 00:59:57,717
<i>Poor Trevor. </i>

921
00:59:59,129 --> 01:00:02,030
Who are you?

922
01:00:06,369 --> 01:00:09,361
Still in the dark?

923
01:00:14,410 --> 01:00:16,469
This game is over.

924
01:00:16,546 --> 01:00:17,774
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

925
01:00:17,847 --> 01:00:20,213
Oh, I hear everything.

926
01:00:20,283 --> 01:00:23,650
And soon you will <i>know</i>
everything...

927
01:00:23,720 --> 01:00:26,712
much more than you want,
I guarantee it.

928
01:00:26,790 --> 01:00:28,951
What is this?

929
01:00:29,025 --> 01:00:31,152
Why are you doing this
to me?

930
01:00:31,227 --> 01:00:34,993
Is it so difficult
to face your demons?

931
01:00:35,064 --> 01:00:38,158
Unh-unh. Y...

932
01:00:38,234 --> 01:00:40,498
None of this is real.

933
01:00:40,570 --> 01:00:41,832
<i>You're</i> not real.

934
01:00:41,905 --> 01:00:44,567
<i>Oh, but I'm afraid</i>
<i>I am. </i>

935
01:00:46,376 --> 01:00:49,607
You can't run
from your past.

936
01:00:54,217 --> 01:00:55,946
You killed them.

937
01:00:56,019 --> 01:00:59,614
<i>You killed Kirsty. </i>

938
01:00:59,689 --> 01:01:03,022
You killed Gwen...
and the others.

939
01:01:03,092 --> 01:01:05,754
<i>You killed them. </i>

940
01:01:05,829 --> 01:01:09,196
And now you're trying
to pin it on <i>me. </i>

941
01:01:09,265 --> 01:01:15,295
The killer is amongst us,
yes.

942
01:01:15,371 --> 01:01:20,001
[Water sloshing]

943
01:01:23,613 --> 01:01:26,138
Ow! Fuck!

944
01:01:36,226 --> 01:01:40,629
God... damn it!

945
01:01:51,908 --> 01:01:55,105
[Groans]

946
01:01:55,178 --> 01:01:57,669
[Seagulls crying]

947
01:02:04,754 --> 01:02:06,517
Where you been, Trev?

948
01:02:06,589 --> 01:02:08,648
Been looking all over
for ya.

949
01:02:15,798 --> 01:02:18,164
Jesus!
What are you doing?

950
01:02:18,234 --> 01:02:19,360
Put that thing away.

951
01:02:19,435 --> 01:02:21,869
Tonight was supposed to be
the night, Trev, remember?

952
01:02:21,938 --> 01:02:24,270
Oh, right, uh,
you don't remember anything.

953
01:02:24,340 --> 01:02:26,433
Well, let me remind you
about your plan.

954
01:02:26,509 --> 01:02:28,875
We'd kill Kirsty,
make it look like a suicide.

955
01:02:28,945 --> 01:02:31,914
You'd get all her money,
and we'd split it 50/50... huh?

956
01:02:31,981 --> 01:02:34,006
None of that's
gonna happen now, is it?

957
01:02:34,083 --> 01:02:36,415
No, you had to go solo with
your little car-accident bit,

958
01:02:36,486 --> 01:02:37,817
and then
you fucked it all up.

959
01:02:37,887 --> 01:02:40,219
What were you thinking, Trev...
that I'd look the other way

960
01:02:40,290 --> 01:02:41,985
and forget
about our little deal?

961
01:02:42,058 --> 01:02:45,118
- I don't know...
- <i>What you're talking about.  I know</i>... <i>heard it. </i>

962
01:02:45,194 --> 01:02:48,925
Gotta tell you, buddy... the amnesia
routine's starting to get a little fuckin' old.

963
01:02:48,998 --> 01:02:50,431
Lange's onto you,

964
01:02:50,500 --> 01:02:54,766
and it's only a matter of time
before he's onto <i>me. </i>

965
01:02:54,837 --> 01:02:58,898
I don't want to spend
the rest of my life in prison.

966
01:02:58,975 --> 01:03:00,909
I'd rather spend it
in Hell...

967
01:03:00,977 --> 01:03:02,103
[Gun cocks]

968
01:03:02,178 --> 01:03:03,805
...with you.

969
01:03:05,348 --> 01:03:07,316
[Gunshot]

970
01:03:07,383 --> 01:03:08,645
[Gun chinks]

971
01:03:09,819 --> 01:03:11,980
[Gasps]

972
01:03:12,855 --> 01:03:15,449
Oh, my God, Bret,
what did you do?

973
01:03:15,525 --> 01:03:17,720
[Seagulls crying]

974
01:03:20,129 --> 01:03:23,621
Oh, God.

975
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:30,703
[Groans]
No, you're not real!

976
01:03:30,773 --> 01:03:33,606
Get out of my head!

977
01:03:33,676 --> 01:03:36,042
[Footsteps running]

978
01:03:39,916 --> 01:03:41,178
[Bell rings]

979
01:03:41,250 --> 01:03:42,842
Sage...

980
01:03:42,919 --> 01:03:44,819
[Groans]

981
01:03:47,690 --> 01:03:48,952
[Door rattles]

982
01:03:49,025 --> 01:03:52,017
Sage...

983
01:04:07,744 --> 01:04:09,541
Oh, no.

984
01:04:09,612 --> 01:04:12,103
Ohh...

985
01:04:24,627 --> 01:04:26,891
[Breathing heavily]

986
01:04:30,533 --> 01:04:32,501
[Doorknob rattles]

987
01:04:32,568 --> 01:04:35,628
[Creaking]

988
01:04:35,705 --> 01:04:38,196
[Rattling]

989
01:04:47,283 --> 01:04:49,183
[Lock disengages]

990
01:04:51,320 --> 01:04:53,686
[Rattling continues]

991
01:04:53,756 --> 01:04:56,156
[Creaking]

992
01:05:02,331 --> 01:05:04,026
[Door creaking]

993
01:05:16,279 --> 01:05:19,680
[Guns cock]

994
01:05:21,651 --> 01:05:23,118
Trevor...

995
01:05:23,186 --> 01:05:25,450
Oh... you don't understand.
I didn't...

996
01:05:25,521 --> 01:05:28,388
Save it.

997
01:05:28,458 --> 01:05:31,427
You don't need
to say a thing.

998
01:05:31,494 --> 01:05:34,224
No, it's, uh...
you know...

999
01:05:34,297 --> 01:05:36,458
You have the right
to remain silent.

1000
01:05:43,406 --> 01:05:44,873
What's going on here,
detective?

1001
01:05:44,941 --> 01:05:47,068
Please, you can't believe
that I did this.

1002
01:05:47,143 --> 01:05:48,235
Detective, believe me.

1003
01:05:48,311 --> 01:05:50,506
I didn't do what
you think I did. Please...

1004
01:05:50,580 --> 01:05:52,138
Relax, Trevor.

1005
01:05:52,215 --> 01:05:54,809
<i>Let's get to the bottom</i>
<i>of this once and for all. </i>

1006
01:05:54,884 --> 01:05:57,819
You want to tell me exactly
what happened back there,

1007
01:05:57,887 --> 01:06:01,050
<i>or should we just play the
headache game a little longer?</i>

1008
01:06:01,124 --> 01:06:03,752
[Telephone rings]

1009
01:06:03,826 --> 01:06:05,589
[Ringing continues]

1010
01:06:05,661 --> 01:06:09,324
Okay.
We'll do it your way.

1011
01:06:09,398 --> 01:06:12,629
This is Lange.

1012
01:06:12,702 --> 01:06:14,761
Really?

1013
01:06:14,837 --> 01:06:19,103
Well, I-I-I got him sitting
right in front of me now.

1014
01:06:19,175 --> 01:06:21,200
[Flogging, man screaming]

1015
01:06:21,277 --> 01:06:23,472
<i>Yes... </i>

1016
01:06:23,546 --> 01:06:24,808
[Flogging, screaming continue]

1017
01:06:24,881 --> 01:06:26,109
<i>Mm-hmm. </i>

1018
01:06:26,182 --> 01:06:27,911
<i>Ugh! Ohh!</i>

1019
01:06:27,984 --> 01:06:29,383
<i>Aggh!</i>

1020
01:06:29,452 --> 01:06:30,680
<i>Ohh!</i>

1021
01:06:30,753 --> 01:06:32,152
<i>Aggh!</i>

1022
01:06:32,221 --> 01:06:33,483
<i>Agggh!</i>

1023
01:06:33,556 --> 01:06:34,682
<i>Thank you. </i>

1024
01:06:34,757 --> 01:06:37,749
Well, one thing's
for sure...

1025
01:06:37,827 --> 01:06:39,351
This ain't
your lucky day.

1026
01:06:40,530 --> 01:06:43,192
They found a body
this morning in the river.

1027
01:06:43,266 --> 01:06:45,666
They're bringing it
into the morgue now

1028
01:06:45,735 --> 01:06:46,997
so you can identify it.

1029
01:06:47,069 --> 01:06:48,627
Is it my wife?

1030
01:06:48,704 --> 01:06:51,730
You stay put.

1031
01:06:54,210 --> 01:06:56,974
[Window blind rattles]

1032
01:06:57,046 --> 01:06:58,809
[Door creaks, closes]

1033
01:06:58,881 --> 01:07:01,873
[Door opens, creaks]

1034
01:07:04,954 --> 01:07:07,218
<i>You know,</i>
<i>I had you pegged for bad</i>

1035
01:07:07,290 --> 01:07:09,451
<i>the minute</i>
<i>I laid eyes on you. </i>

1036
01:07:12,895 --> 01:07:17,195
Now, I want you to tell me
everything you remember happening,

1037
01:07:17,266 --> 01:07:19,826
in your own words, exactly the
way you told Detective Lange,

1038
01:07:19,902 --> 01:07:23,861
but I want you to make
one... minor adjustment.

1039
01:07:23,940 --> 01:07:25,999
What's that?

1040
01:07:26,075 --> 01:07:28,373
Don't fucking lie
to me.

1041
01:07:28,444 --> 01:07:31,208
I just want to see my wife,
man. [Door rushes open]

1042
01:07:43,926 --> 01:07:47,089
I thought I asked you
to stay put.

1043
01:07:49,098 --> 01:07:52,431
<i>Each killed with a single
gunshot wound to the head</i>...

1044
01:07:52,501 --> 01:07:54,901
<i>tortured, then shot. </i>

1045
01:07:54,971 --> 01:07:58,236
<i>We find the gun,</i>
<i>we find the killer. </i>

1046
01:07:58,307 --> 01:08:00,138
This way.

1047
01:08:07,116 --> 01:08:09,414
Sick motherfucker!
Get off me!

1048
01:08:09,485 --> 01:08:12,352
<i>They're gonna fry your ass,</i>
<i>motherfucker!</i>

1049
01:08:12,421 --> 01:08:15,720
I'm gonna wring
your scrawny fuckin' neck!

1050
01:08:15,791 --> 01:08:18,487
Got quite the fan club.

1051
01:08:18,561 --> 01:08:20,586
[Man shouting indistinctly]

1052
01:08:20,663 --> 01:08:22,460
[Electricity crackling]

1053
01:08:22,531 --> 01:08:24,431
Ugh! Agh!

1054
01:08:24,500 --> 01:08:26,400
<i>Agh! Agh!</i>

1055
01:08:26,469 --> 01:08:28,937
Here we go.

1056
01:08:53,562 --> 01:08:55,154
[Buzzer]

1057
01:08:55,231 --> 01:08:56,630
[Click]

1058
01:08:56,699 --> 01:08:58,223
[Buzzer]

1059
01:08:58,301 --> 01:09:00,235
[Door opens]

1060
01:09:00,303 --> 01:09:02,794
[Door creaks]

1061
01:09:02,872 --> 01:09:04,772
[Scream in distance]

1062
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:06,535
[Keys jingle]

1063
01:09:21,991 --> 01:09:24,289
[Muffled screaming]

1064
01:09:24,360 --> 01:09:27,158
[Chains rattling]

1065
01:09:27,229 --> 01:09:29,823
[Trickling]

1066
01:09:38,741 --> 01:09:41,972
Just about there.

1067
01:09:55,725 --> 01:09:57,716
[Water dripping]

1068
01:09:57,793 --> 01:09:59,852
[Screaming continues]

1069
01:10:02,031 --> 01:10:03,396
[Handcuffs click]

1070
01:10:06,202 --> 01:10:07,863
Thanks.

1071
01:10:13,976 --> 01:10:16,342
Whoa. What are you...
[Keys jingling]

1072
01:10:16,412 --> 01:10:18,846
What are you doing?
I thought you believed me.

1073
01:10:18,914 --> 01:10:21,109
Believe?

1074
01:10:21,183 --> 01:10:23,845
Here's what I believe,
Trevor...

1075
01:10:23,919 --> 01:10:27,252
I believe you and me
have a lot in common.

1076
01:10:27,323 --> 01:10:30,656
I believe each of us
are the sum

1077
01:10:30,726 --> 01:10:33,752
of two entirely different
people.

1078
01:10:33,829 --> 01:10:37,356
No.

1079
01:10:37,433 --> 01:10:40,527
I know who I am.

1080
01:10:40,603 --> 01:10:42,230
And I'm not a killer.

1081
01:10:42,304 --> 01:10:44,329
Denial to the end...

1082
01:10:44,407 --> 01:10:49,276
That's what
I like about you, kid!

1083
01:10:49,345 --> 01:10:51,711
Good and bad, Trevor...

1084
01:10:51,781 --> 01:10:53,715
Honest, dishonest...

1085
01:10:53,783 --> 01:10:55,614
Righteous and evil...

1086
01:10:55,684 --> 01:10:59,245
That's how
we're all made.

1087
01:10:59,321 --> 01:11:01,812
It's a little of both.

1088
01:11:01,891 --> 01:11:08,729
It's just a question...
of how much... of each.

1089
01:11:08,798 --> 01:11:12,894
[Crackling]

1090
01:11:19,675 --> 01:11:25,636
And we're made up of just
the right parts of both.

1091
01:11:25,714 --> 01:11:28,205
[Both laugh]

1092
01:11:28,284 --> 01:11:32,550
A little heavy
on the evil, huh?

1093
01:11:32,621 --> 01:11:34,612
<i>[Both laughing]</i>

1094
01:11:38,727 --> 01:11:41,252
It's all good, Trev!

1095
01:11:41,330 --> 01:11:44,060
<i>[Laughing]</i>
<i>It's all good!</i>

1096
01:11:44,133 --> 01:11:46,101
[Laughter continues]

1097
01:11:59,715 --> 01:12:02,912
[Coughs]

1098
01:12:03,986 --> 01:12:06,819
[Coughs]

1099
01:12:20,336 --> 01:12:24,500
[Door rattles, creaks]

1100
01:12:30,279 --> 01:12:32,213
[Door creaks]

1101
01:12:32,281 --> 01:12:33,270
[Door closes]

1102
01:12:52,034 --> 01:12:54,696
[Exhales sharply]

1103
01:12:57,239 --> 01:12:59,139
[Coughs]

1104
01:13:03,979 --> 01:13:06,675
[Flies buzzing]

1105
01:13:21,664 --> 01:13:24,098
[Flies buzzing]

1106
01:13:26,735 --> 01:13:30,000
What the fuck?

1107
01:13:46,755 --> 01:13:48,985
Kirsty?

1108
01:13:55,965 --> 01:13:57,796
[Rumbling]

1109
01:13:57,866 --> 01:13:59,629
[Bottles rattle]

1110
01:14:06,208 --> 01:14:08,802
[Buzzing]

1111
01:14:15,451 --> 01:14:16,713
[Crackles]

1112
01:14:16,785 --> 01:14:17,547
[Squeaks]

1113
01:14:26,328 --> 01:14:28,159
[Rattling]

1114
01:14:28,230 --> 01:14:31,131
[Glass shattering]

1115
01:14:45,748 --> 01:14:48,842
[Electricity crackling]

1116
01:14:58,427 --> 01:15:00,418
[Crackles]

1117
01:15:00,496 --> 01:15:02,623
[Rumbling, rattling subside]

1118
01:15:05,334 --> 01:15:09,430
It seems you've reached
the end of your journey.

1119
01:15:13,342 --> 01:15:17,711
<i>I told you you couldn't
run from your past forever. </i>

1120
01:15:17,780 --> 01:15:20,943
<i>Eventually,</i>
<i>it catches up with you,</i>

1121
01:15:21,016 --> 01:15:24,179
and you must atone.

1122
01:15:24,253 --> 01:15:27,654
<i>And now... </i>

1123
01:15:27,723 --> 01:15:31,557
it is time for you
to pay the price.

1124
01:15:31,627 --> 01:15:34,721
<i>You</i> were <i>willing to pay</i>
<i>the price, weren't you?</i>

1125
01:15:34,797 --> 01:15:38,392
[Music box plays]

1126
01:15:38,467 --> 01:15:40,526
I just want to see
my wife.

1127
01:15:40,602 --> 01:15:42,229
In time.

1128
01:15:42,304 --> 01:15:44,135
Let me see my wife.

1129
01:15:44,206 --> 01:15:46,572
I said, "In time"!

1130
01:15:49,745 --> 01:15:51,542
Agh! Aah!

1131
01:15:51,613 --> 01:15:53,080
Aaah!

1132
01:15:55,217 --> 01:15:56,707
Ugh!
[Rips]

1133
01:15:56,785 --> 01:15:58,047
[Breathes heavily]

1134
01:15:58,120 --> 01:15:59,052
[Ripping]

1135
01:15:59,121 --> 01:16:00,986
<i>Agh! Aagh!</i>

1136
01:16:01,056 --> 01:16:03,047
Aagh!

1137
01:16:03,125 --> 01:16:05,992
<i>Agh! Aagh!</i>

1138
01:16:06,061 --> 01:16:07,221
Ohh!

1139
01:16:07,296 --> 01:16:09,491
[Metal clanking]
Ugh!

1140
01:16:09,565 --> 01:16:12,500
[Breathing heavily]

1141
01:16:12,568 --> 01:16:13,500
[Groans]

1142
01:16:13,569 --> 01:16:14,900
[Metal clanks]

1143
01:16:14,970 --> 01:16:16,028
<i>Agh!</i>

1144
01:16:16,105 --> 01:16:18,835
All problems solved?

1145
01:16:18,907 --> 01:16:21,000
Not so simple,
I'm afraid.

1146
01:16:21,076 --> 01:16:25,706
<i>I needed first</i>
<i>to open a door for you. </i>

1147
01:16:27,583 --> 01:16:29,847
You were
an interesting study.

1148
01:16:29,918 --> 01:16:32,079
Aggh!

1149
01:16:32,154 --> 01:16:34,122
Lust, greed, deception...

1150
01:16:34,189 --> 01:16:37,124
Fertile ground,
but rather mundane.

1151
01:16:37,192 --> 01:16:40,593
[Clanking] Let us take
one final journey together.

1152
01:16:40,662 --> 01:16:45,429
Let me help you remember
once and for all.

1153
01:16:45,501 --> 01:16:47,969
<i>Kirsty:</i>
<i>What have you done?</i>

1154
01:16:48,036 --> 01:16:50,527
It's just a puzzle.
Open it up.

1155
01:16:50,606 --> 01:16:52,130
I trusted you.

1156
01:16:52,207 --> 01:16:54,107
I trusted you!
Goddamn it!

1157
01:16:54,176 --> 01:16:55,939
<i>How could you do this</i>
<i>to us?!</i>

1158
01:16:56,011 --> 01:16:58,206
You told me you loved me!

1159
01:16:58,280 --> 01:17:00,077
Just open
the fuckin' box.

1160
01:17:00,149 --> 01:17:03,710
We were uninvited guests at your
little celebration... [Trevor groans]

1161
01:17:03,786 --> 01:17:05,583
Is this what you want?

1162
01:17:07,489 --> 01:17:09,252
...unseen by you.

1163
01:17:10,692 --> 01:17:13,320
I hope it's everything
you want it to be.

1164
01:17:18,066 --> 01:17:21,661
<i>I used you, Trevor. </i>

1165
01:17:21,737 --> 01:17:24,968
You were nothing more
than bait...

1166
01:17:25,040 --> 01:17:30,342
<i>to lure a far more</i>
<i>interesting creature. </i>

1167
01:17:30,412 --> 01:17:33,575
[Clicking]

1168
01:17:36,185 --> 01:17:39,450
Kirsty...

1169
01:17:39,521 --> 01:17:41,284
We meet again.

1170
01:17:41,356 --> 01:17:43,449
[Voice breaking]
How did you find me?

1171
01:17:43,525 --> 01:17:46,426
<i>You opened a door</i>
<i>long ago,</i>

1172
01:17:46,495 --> 01:17:50,625
and it will not be closed
until I get what I came for.

1173
01:17:50,699 --> 01:17:53,167
[Shudders] My soul.

1174
01:17:53,235 --> 01:17:56,136
Aaaaaaaaaaah!

1175
01:17:56,205 --> 01:18:00,107
You solved the puzzle.
You unleashed the power.

1176
01:18:00,175 --> 01:18:02,268
<i>There is no turning back. </i>

1177
01:18:02,344 --> 01:18:05,643
<i>I will not rest</i>
<i>until I get what I want,</i>

1178
01:18:05,714 --> 01:18:09,343
and what I want is you.

1179
01:18:16,225 --> 01:18:20,821
<i>You always knew</i>
<i>this day was coming,</i>

1180
01:18:20,896 --> 01:18:23,228
<i>felt it deep within</i>
<i>your soul. </i>

1181
01:18:23,298 --> 01:18:24,890
Wait!

1182
01:18:24,967 --> 01:18:27,834
[Breathes heavily]
Wait.

1183
01:18:34,676 --> 01:18:37,144
What if I make you
a deal?

1184
01:18:37,212 --> 01:18:39,077
Interesting.

1185
01:18:39,147 --> 01:18:43,550
I will bring you five souls
in exchange for mine.

1186
01:18:43,619 --> 01:18:47,385
You would bring them
to me yourself?

1187
01:18:47,456 --> 01:18:49,390
You'll get your five.

1188
01:18:49,458 --> 01:18:53,519
<i>I was impressed</i>
<i>with her handiwork. </i>

1189
01:18:53,595 --> 01:18:56,428
Three of your favorite
companions,

1190
01:18:56,498 --> 01:18:58,728
most supple
and delicious...

1191
01:19:00,235 --> 01:19:01,759
...and the man with whom

1192
01:19:01,837 --> 01:19:04,328
you once conspired
to kill Kirsty...

1193
01:19:04,907 --> 01:19:08,001
They are all with <i>me</i> now.

1194
01:19:08,076 --> 01:19:11,011
<i>But the balance</i>
<i>is only four souls,</i>

1195
01:19:11,079 --> 01:19:15,539
and that, as you now know,
was <i>not</i> our contract.

1196
01:19:15,617 --> 01:19:18,108
- Agh! Ugh!
- <i>You have seen many things... </i>

1197
01:19:18,186 --> 01:19:20,586
that you will wish
you had not...

1198
01:19:20,656 --> 01:19:22,920
All those women...

1199
01:19:22,991 --> 01:19:26,791
<i>in our home... </i>
<i>in my bed. </i>

1200
01:19:26,862 --> 01:19:30,423
<i>... many nightmares from which</i>
<i>you will never awake. </i>

1201
01:19:30,499 --> 01:19:32,865
- No, Kirsty, come on...
- Don't you lie to me!

1202
01:19:32,935 --> 01:19:34,027
Don't!

1203
01:19:34,102 --> 01:19:35,694
<i>We can make it work,</i>
<i>all right?</i>

1204
01:19:35,771 --> 01:19:37,568
<i>We can put the pieces</i>
<i>back together. </i>

1205
01:19:37,639 --> 01:19:41,097
- You gotta believe me.
- I am done believing! I trusted you!

1206
01:19:41,176 --> 01:19:45,135
I can't believe this shit is
happening, man. I had a fuckin' deal.

1207
01:19:47,783 --> 01:19:52,482
No, you <i>had</i> a deal...

1208
01:19:52,554 --> 01:19:54,954
but I made
a better offer.

1209
01:19:55,023 --> 01:19:57,457
<i>Trevor: Aggh!</i>

1210
01:19:57,526 --> 01:19:59,016
And guess what?

1211
01:20:01,863 --> 01:20:03,228
He took it.

1212
01:20:03,298 --> 01:20:08,463
<i>Welcome to the worst nightmare</i>
<i>of all. </i>

1213
01:20:11,373 --> 01:20:12,840
Reality.

1214
01:20:12,908 --> 01:20:16,435
[Gunshot]
<i>Aaaaaah!</i>

1215
01:20:16,511 --> 01:20:18,138
[Tires screeching]

1216
01:20:18,213 --> 01:20:22,172
<i>Aaaaah!</i>

1217
01:20:25,487 --> 01:20:28,388
[Gurgling]

1218
01:20:28,457 --> 01:20:31,358
[Creaking]

1219
01:20:32,394 --> 01:20:39,197
<i>Aaaaaaaaaah!</i>

1220
01:20:41,336 --> 01:20:44,499
[Chains rattle]
[Gasps]

1221
01:20:44,573 --> 01:20:47,235
[Breathes heavily]

1222
01:20:49,344 --> 01:20:53,007
[Water dripping slowly]

1223
01:21:13,568 --> 01:21:15,297
Fuck.

1224
01:21:18,874 --> 01:21:22,708
[Voice breaking]
I'm the fifth soul.

1225
01:21:24,980 --> 01:21:27,949
<i>[Siren wails]</i>

1226
01:21:29,985 --> 01:21:32,545
Yeah, that's him.

1227
01:21:32,621 --> 01:21:35,055
[Helicopter whirring]

1228
01:21:35,123 --> 01:21:37,421
Okay, people.
That's it.

1229
01:21:37,492 --> 01:21:39,221
[Indistinct talking]

1230
01:21:39,294 --> 01:21:41,319
[Camera shutter clicking]

1231
01:21:41,396 --> 01:21:44,160
He just shot himself.

1232
01:21:44,232 --> 01:21:46,166
Next thing I knew,
we were in the water.

1233
01:21:46,234 --> 01:21:48,600
There...
I couldn't see anything.

1234
01:21:51,640 --> 01:21:53,608
I lost him.

1235
01:21:53,675 --> 01:21:55,666
You did what you could.

1236
01:21:55,744 --> 01:21:57,575
I'm sorry.

1237
01:21:57,646 --> 01:21:59,841
It just doesn't make
any sense...

1238
01:21:59,948 --> 01:22:03,076
that he would be capable
of murder.

1239
01:22:03,151 --> 01:22:06,382
We found the gun in your car.
It appears to be the same.

1240
01:22:06,455 --> 01:22:10,323
If it matches, I think we
may have found our killer.

1241
01:22:10,392 --> 01:22:12,451
Come on.

1242
01:22:13,895 --> 01:22:16,159
<i>Wait a minute, guys,</i>
<i>before you zip him up. </i>

1243
01:22:16,231 --> 01:22:18,893
[Camera shutter clicking]

1244
01:22:18,967 --> 01:22:20,059
Hmm.

1245
01:22:20,135 --> 01:22:22,103
Wasn't your lucky day,
was it?

1246
01:22:22,170 --> 01:22:25,867
You checked the oral cavity
for blockages?

1247
01:22:25,941 --> 01:22:29,570
Oh, what do we got here?

1248
01:22:38,386 --> 01:22:41,787
And we have a winner.

1249
01:22:46,394 --> 01:22:48,885
Okay, zip it up.
We'll finish at the morgue.

1250
01:22:48,964 --> 01:22:51,330
Wait. Wait.

1251
01:22:51,399 --> 01:22:53,833
[Seagulls crying]

1252
01:22:53,902 --> 01:22:57,099
Sorry I had to leave you
like that for a minute, Trev,

1253
01:22:57,172 --> 01:22:58,434
but I'm back.

1254
01:22:58,507 --> 01:23:01,237
<i>Can you hear me, Trevor?</i>

1255
01:23:01,309 --> 01:23:03,277
Jesus, Allison.

1256
01:23:03,345 --> 01:23:06,075
What possesses you
to talk to cadavers?

1257
01:23:06,148 --> 01:23:07,740
What if
there's no afterlife?

1258
01:23:07,816 --> 01:23:09,875
Wouldn't you want someone
to talk to <i>you</i>

1259
01:23:09,951 --> 01:23:12,784
like a normal human being
one last time?

1260
01:23:12,854 --> 01:23:15,118
[Indistinct talking
on police radio]

1261
01:23:15,190 --> 01:23:17,658
[Siren wailing]

1262
01:23:17,726 --> 01:23:20,627
<i>You're creeping me out,</i>

